WEBVTT

1
00:00:16.875 --> 00:00:20.166
<i>I've checked. and I'm sure. Harry.</i>

2
00:00:20.250 --> 00:00:21.208
<i>The son?</i>

3
00:00:22.416 --> 00:00:24.750
He is our serial killer.

4
00:00:24.833 --> 00:00:26.000
<i>Okay.</i>

5
00:00:27.708 --> 00:00:30.625
Thank you. Beate.
His name is Martin Aminov.

6
00:00:31.208 --> 00:00:35.541
Forty-three. Norwegian citizen. living
in Prague. has a sentence for smuggling.

7
00:00:35.625 --> 00:00:39.750
He has given his mom a diamond identical
to the ones we've found on the victims.

8
00:00:39.833 --> 00:00:43.791
According to his mom. he's been
in Oslo to visit her on all of the dates.

9
00:00:44.625 --> 00:00:45.833
At Villa Valle.

10
00:00:45.916 --> 00:00:46.750
His mother?

11
00:00:46.833 --> 00:00:50.458
She lives under the fifth point.
and she's expecting him tonight.

12
00:00:50.541 --> 00:00:54.041
Backup is already on their way.
and my car is parked over there.

13
00:00:56.041 --> 00:00:57.916
No. wait. wait. wait!

14
00:00:59.916 --> 00:01:02.708
Sit down. No one does anything
until I say so.

15
00:01:04.083 --> 00:01:05.541
Stop the car that's going there.

16
00:01:06.250 --> 00:01:09.291
I don't want a single police car
within one kilometer of that house.

17
00:01:09.375 --> 00:01:13.000
If he gets a whiff of trouble.
we won't get a second chance.

18
00:01:13.583 --> 00:01:17.583
Falkeid. you and your men stay here
until I give you a different command.

19
00:01:17.666 --> 00:01:20.083
- You said--
- I'm the one in charge!

20
00:01:20.958 --> 00:01:23.625
It's on my head if something goes wrong.

21
00:01:23.708 --> 00:01:26.666
That's why I want to deal with it
on my own. Is that understood?

22
00:01:30.041 --> 00:01:32.583
Harry. you stay here and take command.

23
00:01:39.250 --> 00:01:41.625
<i>Hey. Hole. We're on our way
to Villa Valle now.</i>

24
00:01:41.708 --> 00:01:43.583
<i>- Abort backup.
- Abort?</i>

25
00:01:43.666 --> 00:01:47.416
<i>- Waaler will deal with it alone.
- But we're five minutes away--</i>

26
00:01:47.500 --> 00:01:48.666
Just do it.

27
00:01:54.208 --> 00:01:55.958
Alpha to all units. stand by.

28
00:03:09.541 --> 00:03:10.541
Are you armed?

29
00:03:12.041 --> 00:03:14.000
On this mission we are.

30
00:03:16.333 --> 00:03:18.708
Did he mention when he was coming?

31
00:03:18.791 --> 00:03:21.750
Well. he wanted
to take care of something first. he said.

32
00:03:21.833 --> 00:03:24.500
Does he have a key to the front door?

33
00:03:25.416 --> 00:03:27.916
I don't lock the door
when I know he's coming.

34
00:03:28.000 --> 00:03:29.500
Isn't the door locked?

35
00:03:29.583 --> 00:03:30.625
No.

36
00:03:47.125 --> 00:03:48.208
You can lower it now.

37
00:03:50.375 --> 00:03:51.208
Hi.

38
00:03:51.875 --> 00:03:52.875
Mrs. Aminov.

39
00:04:02.750 --> 00:04:04.041
Where's the rest?

40
00:04:04.125 --> 00:04:05.708
It's just you and me.

41
00:04:13.750 --> 00:04:15.791
What do you think you're doing?

42
00:04:17.500 --> 00:04:18.750
What do you mean?

43
00:04:18.833 --> 00:04:20.875
You're standing by the window.

44
00:04:22.416 --> 00:04:24.458
- Oh...
- How long have you been standing there?

45
00:04:24.541 --> 00:04:26.958
Fucking amateur. Into the kitchen.

46
00:04:27.833 --> 00:04:29.083
Into the kitchen.

47
00:04:32.666 --> 00:04:35.458
Stay here. no matter what happens.

48
00:04:35.541 --> 00:04:36.666
Is that understood?

49
00:04:58.250 --> 00:04:59.333
What's that?

50
00:04:59.916 --> 00:05:02.625
Fourth floor. third door on the right.

51
00:05:09.166 --> 00:05:10.083
Oh. fuck...

52
00:05:15.375 --> 00:05:18.458
Falkeid. get your team ready to enter 406.

53
00:05:27.166 --> 00:05:28.250
<i>Charlie 2 responding.</i>

54
00:05:28.916 --> 00:05:32.166
Prepare to enter apartment 406.
Hole is on his way now.

55
00:05:32.958 --> 00:05:33.833
<i>Roger.</i>

56
00:05:36.583 --> 00:05:37.666
Give me a gun.

57
00:05:55.541 --> 00:05:57.500
BACK IN FOUR WEEKS
JULY 7TH - MARIUS

58
00:06:14.416 --> 00:06:15.875
- Clear.
- Clear!

59
00:07:02.500 --> 00:07:03.541
Fuck...

60
00:07:30.291 --> 00:07:32.250
Why do you think it's here. Harry?

61
00:07:33.583 --> 00:07:35.625
Because this is the fifth floor.

62
00:07:50.958 --> 00:07:52.000
Hole?

63
00:08:48.750 --> 00:08:50.916
Yes. Harry?

64
00:08:51.541 --> 00:08:56.083
We were wrong. We found Marius Veland
vacuum sealed in the attic.

65
00:08:56.166 --> 00:08:58.416
He wasn't the next victim.
he was the first.

66
00:08:58.500 --> 00:09:01.333
Aminov started with the thumb
and worked his way down the hand.

67
00:09:02.333 --> 00:09:05.750
Now. there's only the little finger left.
And he's on his way here.

68
00:09:06.583 --> 00:09:11.208
Why is only Waaler here
and not the whole fucking team?

69
00:09:13.333 --> 00:09:16.500
He said that he was worried
we'd scare him off.

70
00:09:20.208 --> 00:09:22.625
He told me to stay here

71
00:09:23.375 --> 00:09:25.750
<i>the same way he told you to stay there.</i>

72
00:09:26.375 --> 00:09:28.416
Harry. what the fuck is going on?

73
00:09:28.500 --> 00:09:29.791
<i>I don't know.</i>

74
00:09:31.416 --> 00:09:32.250
Hey...

75
00:09:33.666 --> 00:09:34.500
Be careful.

76
00:09:36.500 --> 00:09:37.875
I have to go back inside.

77
00:10:43.375 --> 00:10:44.375
Police!

78
00:10:47.500 --> 00:10:49.541
Drop the gun!

79
00:10:51.916 --> 00:10:53.750
I said. drop the gun!

80
00:10:57.208 --> 00:11:00.041
Final warning! Drop the gun!

81
00:11:18.625 --> 00:11:21.375
Tom. what the fuck are you doing?
He's unarmed.

82
00:11:26.416 --> 00:11:30.166
He's unarmed because I disarmed him.

83
00:11:35.083 --> 00:11:37.250
Cuff him!

84
00:11:38.541 --> 00:11:40.958
Stand against the wall! Put down the bag.

85
00:11:42.791 --> 00:11:43.875
Put down the bag!

86
00:12:46.666 --> 00:12:50.125
[Swedish]
<i>I'm on my way back. Back to my uterus.</i>

87
00:12:50.208 --> 00:12:54.583
<i>There I'll lift the knife
and cut my way in.</i>

88
00:13:00.250 --> 00:13:03.000
Fuck me. what a fucking lunatic.

89
00:13:04.666 --> 00:13:06.916
Aminov is an ex-convict. right?

90
00:13:08.791 --> 00:13:09.666
Mm.

91
00:13:10.750 --> 00:13:11.875
Fingerprints?

92
00:13:11.958 --> 00:13:13.541
We don't have the results yet.

93
00:13:16.625 --> 00:13:18.708
Has Martin Aminov confessed?

94
00:13:18.791 --> 00:13:23.000
The suspect has just been through
initial questioning. so it's a process.

95
00:13:23.083 --> 00:13:26.583
Detective Tom Waaler here
is the one who's talking to him.

96
00:13:26.666 --> 00:13:30.750
As you know. this type of interrogation
is a mix of facts and building trust.

97
00:13:30.833 --> 00:13:32.958
Until he's finished. I don't have answers.

98
00:13:33.041 --> 00:13:35.458
Did you find weapons
and diamonds in Aminov's bag.

99
00:13:35.541 --> 00:13:38.083
and are the diamonds identical
to those on the victims?

100
00:13:38.166 --> 00:13:40.208
- Yes. I can confirm that.
<i>- VG'</i> s turn.

101
00:13:40.291 --> 00:13:43.708
Is it true that the body was
vacuum sealed when you found him?

102
00:13:45.041 --> 00:13:46.458
I can't comment on that.

103
00:13:46.541 --> 00:13:50.250
But you can confirm that it is the
Bike Courier Killer you have arrested?

104
00:13:50.333 --> 00:13:54.125
Unfortunately. I cannot confirm any more
than what I've already told you.

105
00:13:54.208 --> 00:13:57.125
But are you happy that the hunt is over?

106
00:13:58.166 --> 00:14:00.166
We don't reply to trick questions.

107
00:14:01.333 --> 00:14:02.500
<i>Dagbladet's</i> turn.

108
00:14:02.583 --> 00:14:06.625
Is it true that the arrest conducted
by Tom Waaler was quite a dramatic one?

109
00:14:07.208 --> 00:14:10.458
I mean. dramatic... I simply did my job.

110
00:14:10.958 --> 00:14:13.500
Do you know if he'd planned to kill again?

111
00:14:13.583 --> 00:14:16.791
Well. it's hard to say.
but of course it's possible.

112
00:14:20.750 --> 00:14:23.000
Holy shit. He'll be a celebrity now.

113
00:14:23.541 --> 00:14:26.500
The man who... led the investigation

114
00:14:26.583 --> 00:14:29.541
and arrested the Bike Courier Killer
all on his own.

115
00:14:32.458 --> 00:14:36.041
We've found fingerprints
in Marius Veland's apartment

116
00:14:36.125 --> 00:14:39.250
matching the TV shop
and Camilla Loen's apartment.

117
00:14:39.333 --> 00:14:43.500
and now we've found the same prints
in Lisbeth Barli's stairway.

118
00:14:43.583 --> 00:14:45.125
Matching Martin Aminov's?

119
00:14:45.208 --> 00:14:48.791
No. That's the crazy part.
It belongs to Veland.

120
00:14:50.250 --> 00:14:54.750
So he's been bringing the thumb
to all the different crime scenes?

121
00:14:54.833 --> 00:14:56.125
Yeah. clearly.

122
00:14:57.666 --> 00:14:58.791
Yeah.

123
00:14:58.875 --> 00:15:00.166
It's elegant.

124
00:15:00.250 --> 00:15:01.708
Yeah. it's certainly elegant.

125
00:15:03.833 --> 00:15:07.250
Some of us are going to Boxer
to celebrate. Are you coming?

126
00:15:07.333 --> 00:15:08.416
Yes.

127
00:15:09.833 --> 00:15:11.083
Are you coming?

128
00:15:11.166 --> 00:15:14.291
No. I've celebrated enough for a lifetime.

129
00:15:14.833 --> 00:15:17.083
Besides. I'm not on the team anymore.

130
00:15:17.666 --> 00:15:18.583
What?

131
00:15:18.666 --> 00:15:20.666
Today is my last day.

132
00:15:21.833 --> 00:15:23.833
What the fuck are you going to do now?

133
00:15:24.416 --> 00:15:25.500
Something else.

134
00:15:27.125 --> 00:15:29.166
Something completely different.

135
00:15:57.583 --> 00:15:59.500
The summer I turned 20.

136
00:15:59.583 --> 00:16:02.500
I went down to Strömstad
to see my best friend Solo.

137
00:16:02.583 --> 00:16:05.958
And then we stole his dad's car
and came here. to Oslo.

138
00:16:07.291 --> 00:16:09.666
We were totally broke.

139
00:16:09.750 --> 00:16:14.166
So we couldn't afford a hotel.
so we slept in the park in sleeping bags.

140
00:16:14.750 --> 00:16:18.416
We walked along Karl Johan Street
during the day. looking at girls.

141
00:16:19.875 --> 00:16:22.166
I lost my virginity in that sleeping bag.

142
00:16:24.125 --> 00:16:27.208
I think that's when I decided
that this was my city.

143
00:16:29.375 --> 00:16:30.708
We were 20. but...

144
00:16:33.250 --> 00:16:34.875
it felt like we had it all.

145
00:16:39.375 --> 00:16:42.500
Marius Veland. Barbara Svendsen.

146
00:16:42.583 --> 00:16:46.250
Camilla Loen. Lisbeth Barli.
They were in their 20s when they died.

147
00:16:46.333 --> 00:16:48.333
They hadn't been truly disappointed yet.

148
00:16:51.541 --> 00:16:53.083
I just spoke to Aminov.

149
00:16:53.666 --> 00:16:56.166
He's a cold. intelligent bastard.

150
00:16:56.250 --> 00:16:59.250
He'll claim insanity. so he won't go
to jail. but to a psych ward.

151
00:16:59.333 --> 00:17:02.958
There. he'll have progress.
A few years later. he'll be discharged.

152
00:17:04.583 --> 00:17:06.583
That's how things are now. We...

153
00:17:07.416 --> 00:17:10.166
don't tidy up the human garbage.

154
00:17:10.250 --> 00:17:13.875
we just skirt around it. put it
in the corner. brush it under the carpet.

155
00:17:13.958 --> 00:17:18.250
And then. we're surprised
when the whole house stinks

156
00:17:18.333 --> 00:17:21.666
like an infected rat's nest.

157
00:17:22.958 --> 00:17:26.041
Someone has to clean up the shit

158
00:17:27.125 --> 00:17:29.500
so that everybody else can breathe freely.

159
00:17:29.583 --> 00:17:30.750
Do you get me?

160
00:17:31.833 --> 00:17:32.958
So far.

161
00:17:34.750 --> 00:17:36.041
So that is what we do.

162
00:17:37.000 --> 00:17:38.333
We take responsibility.

163
00:17:42.125 --> 00:17:44.458
Your first mission has been determined.

164
00:17:44.541 --> 00:17:48.416
If you can do this...
all your problems will be solved.

165
00:17:48.500 --> 00:17:49.666
Your job. everything.

166
00:17:50.750 --> 00:17:52.416
But... what do you mean?

167
00:17:52.916 --> 00:17:53.958
Aminov.

168
00:17:55.000 --> 00:17:55.958
He's garbage.

169
00:17:56.500 --> 00:17:57.458
He must go.

170
00:18:07.750 --> 00:18:09.166
KGB developed it.

171
00:18:10.000 --> 00:18:12.958
It's mostly known as
what Chechen soldiers used

172
00:18:13.041 --> 00:18:15.125
when captured
and looking to kill themselves.

173
00:18:15.208 --> 00:18:17.041
It breaks down the cell walls.

174
00:18:17.125 --> 00:18:20.916
you bleed from every orifice.
and then you bleed to death in seconds.

175
00:18:21.500 --> 00:18:23.583
Tasteless. One ampoule in a glass.

176
00:18:24.333 --> 00:18:26.875
So it's supposed to look like a suicide?

177
00:18:26.958 --> 00:18:31.458
We've realized you have
to bend and break the law

178
00:18:31.541 --> 00:18:33.541
to protect society at large.

179
00:18:35.375 --> 00:18:38.291
Aminov will be in custody
until midnight tomorrow.

180
00:18:38.375 --> 00:18:39.833
Then. he'll be moved.

181
00:18:40.625 --> 00:18:42.250
They know that you're coming.

182
00:18:52.250 --> 00:18:53.083
Right.

183
00:18:53.666 --> 00:18:54.625
Good luck.

184
00:19:39.833 --> 00:19:41.000
Mom!

185
00:19:42.125 --> 00:19:43.625
Harry's brought flowers!

186
00:19:47.208 --> 00:19:48.291
I'm coming.

187
00:20:01.083 --> 00:20:02.333
You're beautiful.

188
00:20:17.250 --> 00:20:18.458
Yeah. so...

189
00:20:19.250 --> 00:20:20.666
Sorry. I...

190
00:20:21.500 --> 00:20:22.375
Thank you.

191
00:20:31.416 --> 00:20:35.000
- Should we put these in water?
- Yes. you should do that.

192
00:20:36.041 --> 00:20:38.125
Was it a bit much to bring flowers?

193
00:20:39.041 --> 00:20:40.458
- Maybe.
- Maybe.

194
00:20:50.208 --> 00:20:51.333
Hi. Harry.

195
00:20:51.916 --> 00:20:53.916
Harry. Maya Ek. <i>Aftenposten.</i>

196
00:20:54.000 --> 00:20:56.083
We're asking people what they think

197
00:20:56.166 --> 00:20:58.625
about the man
kidnapping Barli being caught.

198
00:20:58.708 --> 00:20:59.916
No. thank you.

199
00:21:00.000 --> 00:21:02.416
I actually wanted to ask you
about something else.

200
00:21:03.000 --> 00:21:04.791
Really quick. You...

201
00:21:04.875 --> 00:21:09.000
As a police officer. you've worked
with Tom Waaler for years. Is that so?

202
00:21:09.083 --> 00:21:10.500
I'm not police anymore.

203
00:21:10.583 --> 00:21:13.250
I see. But why...
Can you say anything about Tom?

204
00:21:13.333 --> 00:21:14.750
Hey. just wait a second.

205
00:21:15.666 --> 00:21:17.083
Do you have a business card?

206
00:21:20.708 --> 00:21:22.083
You can reach me anytime.

207
00:21:23.583 --> 00:21:25.041
- Anytime.
- Thank you.

208
00:21:29.333 --> 00:21:32.375
What was that about you not being
a police officer anymore?

209
00:21:33.208 --> 00:21:35.708
My last day at work was yesterday.

210
00:21:38.083 --> 00:21:39.500
But what...

211
00:21:40.625 --> 00:21:42.166
What are you going to do now?

212
00:21:43.541 --> 00:21:44.541
Something else.

213
00:21:47.666 --> 00:21:48.791
<i>Ladies and gentlemen.</i>

214
00:21:48.875 --> 00:21:51.750
- Time for theater.
<i>- The show begins in five minutes.</i>

215
00:21:51.833 --> 00:21:54.083
<i>Please find your seats.</i>

216
00:22:57.125 --> 00:23:01.666
So you think that <i>Pygmalion</i> is about

217
00:23:02.541 --> 00:23:06.250
you ultimately not understanding
why you love somebody?

218
00:23:08.083 --> 00:23:10.875
Well. now you've made me
sound very simple.

219
00:23:10.958 --> 00:23:12.625
- That is what you said.
- Yeah.

220
00:23:12.708 --> 00:23:15.625
Yeah. I'm not very good at theater.

221
00:23:16.500 --> 00:23:17.583
Yeah...

222
00:23:24.666 --> 00:23:26.083
I've received an offer.

223
00:23:28.791 --> 00:23:31.708
So I've agreed
to become a partner in the firm.

224
00:23:35.833 --> 00:23:36.833
Congratulations.

225
00:23:36.916 --> 00:23:38.083
Thank you.

226
00:23:41.791 --> 00:23:44.708
- Was that the thing you wanted to tell me?
- No.

227
00:23:47.916 --> 00:23:50.458
Oleg told me
that he stole that bottle of wine.

228
00:23:51.708 --> 00:23:54.708
And that you picked him up
and brought him home.

229
00:23:55.375 --> 00:23:59.500
And then. he told me
about the bet you made.

230
00:24:01.541 --> 00:24:05.375
The one about him never...
never drinking again...

231
00:24:06.000 --> 00:24:07.625
if you didn't either.

232
00:24:12.625 --> 00:24:14.125
He's grown to love you.

233
00:24:16.000 --> 00:24:19.291
Like... really love you.

234
00:24:22.666 --> 00:24:23.958
And I know that...

235
00:24:26.208 --> 00:24:27.916
That the odds are terrible.

236
00:24:30.666 --> 00:24:32.541
But I'll join you on that bet.

237
00:24:36.583 --> 00:24:38.791
Well... if you want me to.

238
00:24:52.333 --> 00:24:53.583
I love you.

239
00:25:07.791 --> 00:25:09.291
And you love me.

240
00:25:14.250 --> 00:25:15.208
Yes.

241
00:25:18.666 --> 00:25:19.666
I love you.

242
00:25:25.916 --> 00:25:26.916
I know.

243
00:25:30.250 --> 00:25:31.500
Let's go inside.

244
00:25:32.166 --> 00:25:33.500
Hey...

245
00:25:35.625 --> 00:25:38.291
I just have one last thing I need to do.

246
00:25:39.416 --> 00:25:40.750
- At work.
- That's okay.

247
00:25:41.875 --> 00:25:43.333
I'll leave the door unlocked.

248
00:25:44.458 --> 00:25:45.541
No. don't do that.

249
00:25:47.041 --> 00:25:49.125
Um... keep it locked.

250
00:25:50.375 --> 00:25:51.416
For tonight.

251
00:26:26.666 --> 00:26:29.416
Hey. it's me. Can you hit "record"?

252
00:27:44.375 --> 00:27:45.791
Good evening. Aminov.

253
00:27:46.875 --> 00:27:48.208
I'm Detective Hole.

254
00:27:49.958 --> 00:27:52.750
Could you... give me your hands?

255
00:28:12.208 --> 00:28:13.375
Would you like one?

256
00:28:15.875 --> 00:28:18.000
Is this your "good cop" trick?

257
00:28:20.333 --> 00:28:21.291
Yes.

258
00:28:32.041 --> 00:28:35.916
You seem very calm for a man
who's been arrested for four murders.

259
00:28:37.916 --> 00:28:39.125
I'm innocent.

260
00:28:41.916 --> 00:28:45.666
We found a diamond that is identical
to those that were found on the bodies.

261
00:28:45.750 --> 00:28:47.541
We also found a Ceska zbrojovka.

262
00:28:47.625 --> 00:28:50.833
which is the same weapon
that was used to kill Barbara Svendsen.

263
00:28:50.916 --> 00:28:54.250
You've said that you were in Prague
on the dates of the murders.

264
00:28:54.333 --> 00:28:59.416
We've checked. You've made a quick stop
in Oslo on each of those dates.

265
00:28:59.500 --> 00:29:03.166
So. how are your alibis
around five o'clock those dates. really?

266
00:29:06.208 --> 00:29:07.666
Didn't think so.

267
00:29:13.458 --> 00:29:14.458
Anything else?

268
00:29:16.333 --> 00:29:19.375
The guns we found in your suitcase
had the same file marks

269
00:29:19.458 --> 00:29:23.625
as practically all unregistered guns
we've got in this city.

270
00:29:25.208 --> 00:29:30.083
It's almost as if... some kind
of smuggling ring was behind it.

271
00:29:31.291 --> 00:29:32.583
Interesting theory.

272
00:29:35.791 --> 00:29:37.541
Are you smuggling guns for Waaler?

273
00:29:37.625 --> 00:29:39.916
Are the police doing
that sort of stuff too?

274
00:30:14.416 --> 00:30:17.500
When Waaler arrested you. he had two guns.

275
00:30:17.583 --> 00:30:21.000
A service gun
and what he says was your Ceska.

276
00:30:21.083 --> 00:30:23.458
But you were unarmed. isn't that right?

277
00:30:30.541 --> 00:30:31.541
Hi. Martin.

278
00:30:31.625 --> 00:30:34.916
Hi. Tom. What are you doing here?

279
00:30:36.500 --> 00:30:37.833
What the fuck?

280
00:30:38.333 --> 00:30:40.000
Tom. stop it.

281
00:30:44.958 --> 00:30:46.500
What's going on?

282
00:30:50.250 --> 00:30:51.083
Police!

283
00:30:54.458 --> 00:30:59.916
When I told him the Bike Courier
Killer's name was Martin Aminov...

284
00:31:00.916 --> 00:31:02.250
he was terrified.

285
00:31:03.583 --> 00:31:06.000
He wasn't afraid
another murder would happen.

286
00:31:07.541 --> 00:31:08.750
He was afraid of you.

287
00:31:11.000 --> 00:31:11.833
You know him.

288
00:31:14.541 --> 00:31:16.375
You're one of his runners.

289
00:31:17.833 --> 00:31:22.041
Tom Waaler knows that if you get charged
with the murders that you have committed.

290
00:31:22.125 --> 00:31:26.166
you will do everything you can
to make some sort of deal.

291
00:31:27.166 --> 00:31:31.166
You will tell everything
about him and the network.

292
00:31:32.666 --> 00:31:35.833
So it's a much better idea
to simply shoot you.

293
00:31:40.166 --> 00:31:41.750
You don't believe me.

294
00:31:53.291 --> 00:31:55.916
Do you think that Tom Waaler
will save you from this?

295
00:32:00.500 --> 00:32:04.500
Like some sort of reward
for your collaboration?

296
00:32:07.833 --> 00:32:11.583
<i>Or do think you have so much on him
that you can pressure him into helping?</i>

297
00:32:15.458 --> 00:32:17.291
I thought you were a smart guy.

298
00:32:18.208 --> 00:32:21.000
You've been one step
ahead of us this whole time.

299
00:32:21.500 --> 00:32:24.416
and you can't even see how Waaler thinks.

300
00:32:32.416 --> 00:32:34.125
You're right. I don't believe you.

301
00:32:36.791 --> 00:32:38.208
Hey. how...

302
00:32:39.458 --> 00:32:40.750
How was the water?

303
00:32:42.583 --> 00:32:44.041
It tastes like water.

304
00:32:44.125 --> 00:32:45.166
Right.

305
00:32:55.750 --> 00:32:56.666
It's empty.

306
00:32:58.083 --> 00:32:59.000
Bon appétit.

307
00:33:01.375 --> 00:33:02.208
What?

308
00:33:02.833 --> 00:33:04.833
Compliments of Tom Waaler.

309
00:33:12.958 --> 00:33:15.958
Who do you think arranged
for you to stay here unguarded?

310
00:33:16.708 --> 00:33:19.041
You should have been
in a high security prison.

311
00:33:19.125 --> 00:33:22.333
Instead. you're here.
in an ordinary holding cell.

312
00:33:22.416 --> 00:33:26.291
Where anyone with a regular police ID
can get in and out.

313
00:33:26.375 --> 00:33:27.916
just as they please.

314
00:33:32.791 --> 00:33:34.416
I want to make a deal with you.

315
00:33:34.500 --> 00:33:38.125
If you take one of these within
the first ten minutes of a Joseph's.

316
00:33:38.708 --> 00:33:41.208
you have a pretty good chance of survival.

317
00:33:42.416 --> 00:33:44.791
I want you to testify against Waaler.

318
00:33:49.375 --> 00:33:51.208
Yes. I promise. Give it to me.

319
00:33:51.291 --> 00:33:52.500
- Can I trust you?
- Yes!

320
00:33:52.583 --> 00:33:53.708
How do I know that?

321
00:33:54.958 --> 00:33:57.500
I need you to convince me.
do you get that?

322
00:33:58.083 --> 00:33:59.166
Fine.

323
00:33:59.833 --> 00:34:01.916
Preferably before you bleed to death.

324
00:34:02.416 --> 00:34:05.208
Have you ever seen someone
die from that before?

325
00:34:05.875 --> 00:34:07.375
First. they shit themselves.

326
00:34:07.458 --> 00:34:10.916
then blood pours out of every orifice.
even the eyes.

327
00:34:11.000 --> 00:34:14.041
Yes. okay.
You can trust me because it's logical.

328
00:34:14.875 --> 00:34:17.916
If I don't die. Waaler will see
that I've turned against him.

329
00:34:18.000 --> 00:34:20.166
Then. there's no turning back for me.

330
00:34:20.250 --> 00:34:23.416
Either he has to take me out.
or I him. I have no choice.

331
00:34:24.416 --> 00:34:25.916
Okay. keep going.

332
00:34:27.250 --> 00:34:30.708
If I stay in here. I won't stand a chance.

333
00:34:31.250 --> 00:34:35.125
Even if you give me that pill.
someone else will finish the job.

334
00:34:36.250 --> 00:34:37.958
The only way I can survive

335
00:34:39.458 --> 00:34:42.375
is for Waaler to be exposed and arrested.

336
00:34:42.458 --> 00:34:45.375
And you are the only one
who can help me do that right now.

337
00:34:47.500 --> 00:34:49.416
- Good. Congratulations.
- Yeah.

338
00:34:49.500 --> 00:34:51.875
- Get up. turn around.
- Give me the pill.

339
00:34:51.958 --> 00:34:55.458
- No. we're leaving.
- Give me the pill. for fuck's sake!

340
00:34:56.708 --> 00:34:59.625
This is just Flunipam. Sleeping pills.

341
00:35:01.041 --> 00:35:02.166
Come on. get up.

342
00:35:16.625 --> 00:35:18.291
I wouldn't worry too much.

343
00:35:18.791 --> 00:35:22.375
I poured out the contents
of that capsule in the sink. so...

344
00:35:23.083 --> 00:35:26.708
if the water had a funny taste.
take it up with Oslo's Water Department.

345
00:35:50.291 --> 00:35:51.541
What's going on here?

346
00:35:52.041 --> 00:35:56.791
The detainee from 105 is going
to be interrogated on the sixth floor.

347
00:35:56.875 --> 00:35:58.166
Where do I sign him out?

348
00:35:59.750 --> 00:36:01.291
I haven't heard about that.

349
00:36:01.375 --> 00:36:05.041
No. but I don't think we usually
tell you guys about that. Groth.

350
00:36:07.041 --> 00:36:08.500
Hey. relax.

351
00:36:08.583 --> 00:36:10.875
It's just a small change in the plans. He...

352
00:36:11.625 --> 00:36:15.291
He doesn't want to take his medicine.
so we're doing something different.

353
00:36:17.416 --> 00:36:19.875
I have no idea what you're talking about.

354
00:36:20.833 --> 00:36:21.833
No.

355
00:36:22.583 --> 00:36:23.625
Right.

356
00:36:25.500 --> 00:36:29.791
If you have no further questions.
I suggest that you just take out your log.

357
00:36:29.875 --> 00:36:31.208
so that I can sign it.

358
00:36:32.333 --> 00:36:33.291
Brother.

359
00:37:44.083 --> 00:37:45.083
Hello?

360
00:37:45.166 --> 00:37:47.000
<i>It's Groth. I've tried calling you.</i>

361
00:37:47.083 --> 00:37:49.166
Yeah. but I've been working out.

362
00:37:49.250 --> 00:37:52.125
Listen. something's happened here
with that detainee.

363
00:37:52.208 --> 00:37:55.250
<i>Hole came here
to pick him up for an interrogation.</i>

364
00:38:07.541 --> 00:38:08.666
Shit!

365
00:38:29.208 --> 00:38:31.583
Why are you constantly checking the time?

366
00:38:33.791 --> 00:38:35.750
To see when they start pursuing us.

367
00:38:37.833 --> 00:38:39.041
When does that start?

368
00:38:41.875 --> 00:38:43.083
It just started.

369
00:38:48.666 --> 00:38:49.791
Hi.

370
00:38:50.375 --> 00:38:51.791
- Jesus...
- Excuse me.

371
00:38:55.250 --> 00:38:56.250
What do you want?

372
00:38:56.791 --> 00:38:59.625
I just want...
I just wanted to say thank you.

373
00:39:00.250 --> 00:39:01.333
For what?

374
00:39:01.833 --> 00:39:03.291
For that diamond.

375
00:39:24.666 --> 00:39:25.666
Thank you.

376
00:39:52.708 --> 00:39:56.750
POLICE

377
00:40:15.000 --> 00:40:16.416
Beate Lønn.

378
00:40:16.500 --> 00:40:18.708
<i>Hi! I'm sorry if I woke you up. Beate.</i>

379
00:40:18.791 --> 00:40:22.000
<i>This is Maria Aminov calling.</i>

380
00:40:23.458 --> 00:40:25.208
I was just wondering about Martin.

381
00:40:25.791 --> 00:40:28.125
<i>- Yes?</i>
- When do you think I can go see him?

382
00:40:30.458 --> 00:40:32.625
That is very difficult for me to say. but

383
00:40:32.708 --> 00:40:35.208
<i>let me check if and when it's possible.</i>

384
00:40:35.291 --> 00:40:38.250
and I'll call you back
early tomorrow morning.

385
00:40:39.916 --> 00:40:42.375
<i>There's another thing.
It's probably nothing...</i>

386
00:40:42.458 --> 00:40:46.375
I'm worried about my tenant Ina.
She's not been home for days. and...

387
00:40:46.458 --> 00:40:48.291
You have a tenant?

388
00:40:48.375 --> 00:40:51.125
<i>I may have forgotten to say.
She's in the maid's room.</i>

389
00:40:51.208 --> 00:40:55.458
It's on the other side of the back room.
She's not been here for several days.

390
00:40:55.541 --> 00:40:56.500
But...

391
00:40:57.583 --> 00:40:59.416
Where? With whom?

392
00:40:59.500 --> 00:41:02.166
That's what I'd like to know.
I've not met him yet.

393
00:41:02.250 --> 00:41:05.041
<i>She just said
that they were going to his cabin.</i>

394
00:41:11.625 --> 00:41:12.541
<i>Yes?</i>

395
00:41:12.625 --> 00:41:13.791
Hole tricked us.

396
00:41:14.958 --> 00:41:17.250
He took Aminov and disappeared.

397
00:41:17.875 --> 00:41:20.208
<i>This is a big problem. Prince.</i>

398
00:41:20.291 --> 00:41:22.291
<i>And for now. it's your problem.</i>

399
00:41:23.458 --> 00:41:25.541
<i>How are you planning to solve this?</i>

400
00:41:26.666 --> 00:41:28.333
He's a cop.

401
00:41:29.500 --> 00:41:31.666
I have no idea how far I should take this.

402
00:41:33.041 --> 00:41:36.000
<i>At the moment.
you don't have that many options. do you?</i>

403
00:41:37.208 --> 00:41:38.875
<i>I've spoken to the leader.</i>

404
00:41:39.583 --> 00:41:41.083
<i>You are to take out both.</i>

405
00:41:41.958 --> 00:41:43.333
Could you repeat that?

406
00:41:44.958 --> 00:41:47.041
<i>We want you to kill Harry Hole.</i>

407
00:42:04.541 --> 00:42:05.625
Hi. it's me.

408
00:42:06.291 --> 00:42:07.875
I've just spoken with the boss.

409
00:42:08.708 --> 00:42:10.041
<i>We've got a job to finish.</i>

410
00:43:43.541 --> 00:43:48.500
Subtitle translation by: Trine Friis
